thread.title: Asia-Pacific Stocks Head for Biggest Drop in Eight Weeks

author: Joanne Chiu
title: Asia-Pacific Stocks Head for Biggest Drop in Eight Weeks
text:
Despite overnight declines in U.S. stocks on trade worries, major Asian markets started off slightly higher Friday, with gains in Hong Kong’s Hang Seng, Japan’s Nikkei, South Korea’s Kospi and Australia’s S&P 200 capped at less than 0.5%. Nevertheless, MSCI’s Asia-Pacific Index excluding Japan fell 0.5% as it heads for a 1% drop this week, its biggest weekly decline in two months, after last week’s 2.4% rise.
